Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: On a quiet frontier planet, on the edges of the galaxy, our story begins...
Mission.Name: Relic Episode 1 (beta v0.1)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Fascinating. So the rumors were true after all.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action - Set Units Neutral
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(2) for i=1,#units do Spring.SetUnitNeutral(units[i], true) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: To think... Out here on the frontier, on this forgotten world...
A prewar tech lab... and in almost pristine condition, too. Little lab... how long have you been here, waiting for someone to uncover your treasures?

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action - CEG Boom
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local x = 2200 local z = 6150 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z) Spring.SpawnCEG("100rlexplode", x, y, z, 0, 1, 0, 150) Spring.PlaySoundFile("explosion/mini_nuke", 1, x, y, z, "sfx")

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Gah!
Wa ha ha ha ha ha ha! Looks like our intel was right on the money. Now hand over them relics and nobody has to get hurt... wa ha ha ha ha!
Tch. Pirates. Leave it to buzzards like you to show up once someone else has done all the hard work.
Sticks and stones may break my bones, Ms. Explorer, but my plasma blasters will certainly harm you. Now hand over them relics!
Want them so badly, do you? Pry them from the smouldering wreckage of my hull then... if you can!
Fine! We're getting a bigger bounty for this anyway. Get 'er, boys!

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Pirates are attacking you in order to steal your relics. Find some way to get past them and escape.
TriggerLogic.Title: Escape Pirates

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action - Vindi Hold Fire
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("EscapeShip") local unitID for i in pairs(units) do unitID = i end
Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIRE_STATE, {0}, {})

TriggerLogic.Message:
Yeesh. Stupid pirates.
Doubt that was the last of them, though. I better get myself patched up while making plans to get to safety.
Alright, this Caretaker nanoturret will patch the holes in my hull nicely. The LLTs should be able to cover us both for a bit.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Fighting from the high ground is often advantageous; your units gain range while the enemy loses it. They also have to move uphill to attack you, slowing them down and making them easy pickings for ranged weapons.
Note that units with beamlaser weapons, such as the LLT, have spherical range and thus do not shoot further when on a hill (in fact, they can lose coverage). However, it is often still beneficial to place them on elevated positions.

These guys are bloody persistent, aren't they? I need to get to my transport to the northwest and get off this planet.
But first I'll need to get some idea of how many of them are still out there. A Radar Tower should help with that.

TriggerLogic.Description: Construct a radar tower to get a picture of enemy troop movements in the area.
TriggerLogic.Title: Build Radar Tower

TriggerLogic.Message:
Radar indicates the position of nearby enemy units as "dots" or "blips". The position of the dots "wavers" around the unit's true position, so long-range precision weapons are unlikely to hit. Additionally, radar cannot see through terrain, and radar-stealthed/jammed or cloaked units can go undetected by radar.
The Radar Tower also has good visual sight distance in addition to its radar, which can be useful for getting more line-of-sight coverage.

There we go. Maybe if I'd thought to build one of these earlier, those pirates wouldn't have been able to sneak up on me.
There's no telling how many more of them are waiting in the plains for me. My best bet is probably to circle around the mountain to the north and then make a break for it.
Several munitions bunkers are scattered around this region, remnants of the Last War. There's one nearby; maybe it'll have something for me if I open it up.
Warriors. Excellent. These reliable, powerful machines should tear apart any raiders we encounter with ease.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Felon Team") local x = 3150 local z = 6700 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, z}, {"ctrl"} )

local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Felon Team") local x = 5360 local z = 6130 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, z}, {"ctrl", "shift"} )
x = 3400 z = 4800 y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, z}, {"ctrl", "shift"} )

TriggerLogic.Message: Glaives! These were the signature combatants of the Last War, and are still common today. I must admit, watching a charge from a group of these break up a skirmisher formation is rather satisfying.
Alert: Enemy forces are closing in from the rear. Recommendation: Keep moving forward to avoid capture.
Those Rockos are arranged in a line formation. Hitting them from the side will give our units better odds.
Riots and LLTs, huh. Good thing that last bunker happened to be housing a complement of Rogue-class skirmishers.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Felon Team") local x = 1250 local z = 2500 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, z}, {"ctrl", "shift"} )

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local cam = { px = 590, py = 400., pz = 140, rx = math.rad(-5), ry = math.rad(34), mode = 4 } Spring.SetCameraState(cam, 0)

TriggerLogic.Message: Thank goodness. Maybe on the way back I'll have time to carefully inspect what those pirates were so eager to die for.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action -Trans
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("EscapeShip") local unitID for i in pairs(units) do unitID = i end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Self") local targetID for i in pairs(units) do targetID = i end
Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.LOAD_UNITS, {targetID}, {}) local x = Game.mapSizeX - 64 local z = Game.mapSizeZ - 64 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x, y, z}, {"shift"})
local cam = { px = 4172, py = 815, pz = 2658, rx = math.rad(-8), ry = math.rad(239), } Spring.SetCameraState(cam, 0)
